text:
Sir, in that circle thou art nam’d;
Sir, in that circle thou art fam’d;
And some, by whom thy doctrine’s blam’d
(Which gives thee honour)
Yea, sir, by them thy heart is deem’d,
And winning manner.

source_text:
Sir, in that circle you are nam’d;
Sir, in that circle you are fam’d;
An’ some, by whom your doctrine’s blam’d
(Which gies you honour)
Even, sir, by them your heart’s esteem’d,
An’ winning manner.

